Others: Shaedon Sharpe returned to the court after a 9-month absence due to injuries.
Robert Williams III returned to the court after a year-long absence due to a knee injury.
Sharpe played 20 minutes in his first game back, scoring 13 points, grabbing 2 rebounds, assisting once, and blocking once.
Williams played 17 minutes in his first game back, scoring 13 points (4-of-5 FG, 4-of-4 FT), grabbing 3 rebounds, assisting twice, stealing twice, and blocking once.
Sharpe and Williams both showed no lingering effects of their long absences, performing at a high level in their first games back.
